# Domain Knowledge

## Polygon.io conventions

- Stock tickers: plain symbol, e.g. `AAPL`, `MSFT`
- Index tickers use `I:` prefix in the REST API: `I:SPX`, `I:NDX`, `I:VIX` (NOT Norgate's `$$SPX`, NOT `$I:SPX`)
- URL-encode index tickers in URL paths: `quote("I:SPX", safe="")` → `I%3ASPX`
- Always use `adjusted=true` on all stock OHLCV requests and flat files
- Grouped daily endpoint: `GET /v2/aggs/grouped/locale/us/market/stocks/{date}`
- Flat files via S3: `flatfiles.polygon.io` bucket, `us_stocks_sip/day_aggs_v1/`
- Market holidays: Polygon returns empty response — treat as no-data day, do not error

## Trading calendar

- ~252 trading days per year
- Weekdays only, excluding US market holidays
- All dates as `YYYY-MM-DD` strings in DB and API
- Timezone context for daily data: US/Eastern (market close ~4:00 PM ET)

## Key metric formulas

| Metric | Formula |
|---|---|
| `liqfilter` | `MA(close × volume, 20) >= 250,000` |
| `pricefilter` | `close[20] >= 5` |
| `rvol` | `volume / rolling(20).mean(volume)` |
| `ibs` | `(close - low) / (high - low)` |
| `sma_N` | `rolling(N).mean(close)` |
| `atr_N` | `pandas_ta.atr(high, low, close, length=N)` |
| `rsi14` | `pandas_ta.rsi(close, length=14)` |
| `hhv_N` | `rolling(N).max(close)` |
| `llv_N` | `rolling(N).min(close)` |
| `t2108` | `count(close > sma40) / total_stocks` |
| `extremeup` | `close > open AND range > atr21 AND body > 0.5 × range AND advancing` |
| `bu021ok` | `close > open AND close > hhv021[1] AND hhv007[1] < hhv021[1]` |
| `mcclellan` | `ema19 - ema39` where input = `((adv - dec) / (adv + dec)) × 1000` |
| `rat5` | `sum(adv, 5 days) / sum(dec, 5 days)` |

## McClellan EMA rule

McClellan Oscillator requires chronological processing — each day's EMA depends on the prior day. When building historical data, carry `adv_ema19` and `adv_ema39` forward through the date loop. For daily updates, read yesterday's values from `market_summary`.

## Universe and repo grain

- `all`: NYSE + NASDAQ combined, liqfilter + pricefilter applied
- `nyse`: NYSE stocks only
- `nasdaq`: NASDAQ stocks only
- Stock-level data (`daily_metrics`) is never exposed to users — always aggregate first
- Repo grain is set when the aggregation script is written — date only, or date + dimension

## Prices

- All prices in USD
- Volumes in shares (not dollar volume, unless explicitly computing dollar volume)
- RVOL and dollar_volume use 20-day rolling averages as the baseline

## GICS sectors (standard classification)

Technology, Healthcare, Financials, Consumer Discretionary, Consumer Staples,
Industrials, Energy, Materials, Real Estate, Communication Services, Utilities
